author: Ectoid

text: Lots of mentions of Jane Doe. I can tell you that "morgue horror" has been around as long as there has been sound in film. I have seen a film from 1950s black and white that revolved around the same idea, and there have been many variations of this from zombies, ghosts, spirits, vampires... most are not that great. Jane had a few new elements and was definitely one of the better ones. There are a few Asian ones that were good as well. My theory is that it is pretty cheap to film at a college medical morgue as there is nobody there at night and the settings are scary, thus the genre. Of course this mixes the possession horror genre, which there must be hundreds... from really crappy B-films to big ones. Hollywood has no new ideas, and it doesn't need any as long as it can make the film entertaining enough to get people to pay for popcorn (is a very large source of revenue) and rent a seat for 2 hours.
